    {
        "SurahNumber": 48,
        "AyahNumber": 6,
        "Tafseer": "\"And [that] He may punish the hypocrite men and hypocrite women and the polytheist men and polytheist women - those who assume about Allah an assumption of evil. Upon them is a misfortune of evil, and Allah has become angry with them and has cursed them and prepared for them Hell, and evil is it as a destination.\" (6)\n\nThe Other Aspect of Allah's Test\n\nThis describes the other aspect of the test. The test through which Allah Almighty opens the way of great success for the believers is that which necessarily opens the way of destruction, i.e., Hell, for the hypocrite men and women, and the polytheist men and women. This is because their corruption stands manifest, and His proof is established against them.\n\n'those who assume about Allah an assumption of evil' points to those assumptions of the hypocrites which are mentioned below in verse 12 in these words: 'But you thought that the Messenger and the believers would never return to their families, and that was pleasing to your hearts. And you assumed an assumption of evil and became a ruined people.'\n\nSimilarity between the Hypocrites and the Polytheists\n\nConjoining the hypocrite men and women with the polytheist men and women is due to the deep mental and spiritual similarity between them. Just as a polytheist, while claiming bended-servitude to his Lord, worships other deities, similarly, a hypocrite, while claiming faith and obedience to Allah and His messenger, makes conspiracies with others: 'We will obey you in part of the matter' (Muhammad: 26). Due to this sharing, the Qur'an has declared hypocrisy as shirk, which we have explained in our book *Haqiqat-e-Shirk*. Here, by mentioning the hypocrites along with the polytheists, the Qur'an has determined their rank—showing that such claimants of faith will be gathered on the Day of Judgment along with those polytheists with whom they share their way.\n\nAn Eloquent Parenthetical Clause\n\n'Upon them is a misfortune of evil' (alayhim da'irat-us-saw') stands as a parenthetical clause. When their bad assumptions and their bad desires regarding the future of Islam and the Muslims were mentioned, He stated immediately: 'These people are waiting for a bad turn for the Muslims, whereas the bad turn is upon them in reality, because those upon whom they rely will face their end soon, and they will also face this end.' Allah's curse is upon them, He has prepared Hell for them, and wretched is that destination.\n\nThe Wisdom of Mentioning Women side by side with Men\n\nHere, another matter is also worth keeping in view. In the mention of the believers, and then in the mention of the hypocrites and the polytheists, women are mentioned with special care side by side with men. The reason is: this is a comment on the situations of the period of trial. In this period, if hypocrisy is nurtured within any group, a major factor is the family. This is pointed to by the statement of the hypocrites quoted below in verse 11: 'Our properties and our families kept us busy.' And in the Hadith: 'A child is a cause of miserliness and cowardice.' Similarly, if faith is robust within any group, the resolve, patience, and trust of the family have a major share in it. This required that in the mention of both the believers and the hypocrites, the role of women also stood manifest so that both the believing women and the hypocrite women knew: their Lord is not unaware of the devotion of some, and of the self-indulgence of others."
