    {
        "SurahNumber": 48,
        "AyahNumber": 7,
        "Tafseer": "\"And to Allah belong the soldiers of the heavens and the earth, and Allah is ever Exalted in Might and Wise.\" (7)\n\nDisassociation from the Hypocrites\n\nExactly this same clause, with the difference of a single word 'Al-Aziz' (Exalted in Might), has passed in verse 4 above. There, it appeared in a specific context. Here, it is to express disassociation and self-sufficiency from these hypocrites—implying: if these hypocrites wish to become the fuel of Hell, let them; Allah has no need of these cowardly people. All the armies of the heavens and the earth are His. He is dominant over everything, and He is also Wise. Under His wisdom, He can use these armies as He pleases. No one's cowardice can affect His decisions."
